==English==
===Pronunciation===
*stŏk, /stɒk/, /<tt>stQk</tt>/

===Noun===
'''stock''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''stocks''')

#A store of goods ready for sale.
#:''We have a stock of televisions on hand.''
#A species of [[flower]].
#A supply of anything ready for use.
#:''Lay in a stock of wood for the winter season.''
#[[Farm]] [[animals]] or [[equipment]].
#(''also'' '''rolling stock''') [[Railroad]] [[car]]s.
#(''economics'') A [[share]] of a company.
#The part of a [[rifle]] or [[shotgun]] that rests against the shooter's [[shoulder]].
#(''nautical'') A [[bar]] going through an [[anchor]], perpendicular to the [[fluke]]s.
#(''uncountable'') [[Broth]] made from [[meat]] or [[vegetable]]s, used as a basis for [[stew]] or [[soup]].
#A wide [[necktie]] popular in the eighteenth century.
<!--This is "take stock
#An [[estimate]].
#:''He took stock of the situation.''
-->
